  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study has two purposes: firstly, a better understanding of the neurobiological processes
      underlying episodic memory and, secondly, the development of useful clinical applications for
      epileptic patients, in particular the prediction of postoperative memory deficits and the
      development of cognitive remediation therapies.

      Memory performances during a fMRI experiment will be assessed in controls and epileptic
      patients before and after the surgery.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
